lenders.occupational_info:
My full legal name is Ronald Christopher Clark, but most of my family and friends just refer to me as Ron or Ronald. I have been working in Technology in some form for over 20 years.  I started my career in the Technology Field as an 18 year old, straight out of Oak Ridge High School in Tennessee after graduation, in the United States Air Force in 1987.  I did my basic training in San Antonio, Texas and then completed my training as an Avionics Technician in Biloxi, Mississippi and Dover, Delaware.  I served 6 years of active duty and 2 years of inactive duty, primarily oversees @ Yokota Air Force Base in Japan and Rhein Main Air Force Base in Germany from 1987-1995. I am an active minister of the Gospel of Jesus Christ and after serving in the military, I completed a ministerial program @ Rhema Bible Training Center in Broken Arrow, Oklahoma for a year in 1994.  Upon completion of my biblical training, I moved back to Tennessee to make a life as a civilian.  I completed an associates and bachelors program @ ITT Technical Institute in Knoxville at the top of my class in 1998. I’ve worked various jobs in Technology, including Robotics, Manufacturing, Nuclear, Nano-Technologies, Help Desk, Desktop Support, Printer Support, POS and Networking and a brief time in Avionics again with the Air National Guard from 2000-2003 (I am a veteran, obviously as I mentioned earlier, with 2 Honorable Discharges with several honors and accommodations).  As I like to explain to my colleagues and friends, I can work on anything that has a circuit board or electronics contained in it and I have experience working on everything from the older tube technologies to the current microprocessor world. I enjoy helping people, especially teaching and explaining how technology works and how it can be used to assist people toward making their lives easier and more rewarding.  
I am originally from Kentucky and was born and raised in the capital city of Frankfort, Kentucky and partially in rural, Muhlenberg County.  I have been a resident of Tennessee since 1983 when my mother, brother, and I moved from Kentucky to Tennessee to embark on my freshman in high school….I also have roots in Florida (where my father’s people are from) and call Orlando home as well.  I have been married to my wife, Jamesetta, for over 13 years and we both have children from previous relationships.  My daughter, Ronaye Grace (affectionately known as Gracie) is 17 years old and a junior @ Oak Ridge High School and my step-son, Jermaine Williams is 32 years old and is a trucker with Swift Transportation and currently resides in Knoxville, Tennessee (where my wife is from originally).  My wife and I had our first grandbaby, Malaysia, when Jermaine and his fiancé, Nicole, birthed her over a year ago in 2013. Besides technology and my love for the Bible and Jesus Christ, I enjoy watching and playing sports and recently started running and training for 5Ks and I hope to run my first half marathon this year.  I am also a voracious reader of various subjects, especially biographies and autobiographies.  Overall, I am just a passionate, respectful person who enjoys spending time with family, friends, and serving in my community.  I currently reside in Antioch, Tennessee and have been working for CompuCom Systems, first as a consultant in March and hired on permanently in October, and have initially served on the Walmart contract and now with the T-Mobile contract.
